---
import "../styles/tailwind.css";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>You Found the Cozy Corner – NestleIn</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;700&family=Playfair+Display:wght@500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>

  <body class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 via-white to-orange-100 font-sans text-gray-800 min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center px-4 py-20">

    <div class="text-center max-w-lg space-y-6">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif font-medium text-orange-700">✨ You Found the Cozy Corner ✨</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-base max-w-md mx-auto">
        Not many stumble upon this spot... but those who do? They get the goods.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-orange-100 shadow-md">
        <p class="text-orange-700 font-semibold text-sm uppercase mb-2 tracking-wide">Your Secret Tip:</p>
        <p class="text-gray-800 text-sm">The <strong>quietest Wi-Fi oasis</strong> in town? It's usually the place with the worst Yelp photos. Trust the vibe, not the pixels. 😉</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-orange-100 text-orange-700 px-4 py-3 rounded-full inline-block text-sm font-medium mt-4">
        Promo Code: <code class="font-mono">NESTVIBES</code>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <img src="https://illustrations.popsy.co/gray/coffee-break.svg" alt="Cozy coffee illustration" class="w-full max-w-xs mx-auto opacity-90" loading="lazy" />
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="/" class="text-sm text-orange-600 hover:underline">Back to the Main Map</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </body>
</html>
